Loading the Data


data <- read.csv("Data/Final_Dataset.csv", header = T)

Cleaning the Data

We need to modify the data slightly, this includes some basic imputation as well as the creation of a few additional variables.


## New Variables

## State, note that the first two digits (the ten-thousand and thousand place) of the county code are the state code
data$state <- factor(floor(data$county_code/1000))

threshold <- 10
data_counties <- read.table("Data/county_adjacency.txt", sep = '\t', header = F)

cnty <- NA

data$neighbor_synthetic_outbreak <- F
data$neighbor_highest_synthetic_opioid_death_rate <- 0

for(i in 1:nrow(data_counties)){
  
  if(!is.na(data_counties$V2[i])){
    cnty <- data_counties$V2[i]
  }else{
    data_counties$V2[i] <- cnty
  }
  
}


for(fips in unique(data_counties$V2)){
  
  neighbors <- data_counties[data_counties$V2 == fips,][-1,]
  
  
  for(year in 2010:2017){
    highest <- 0
    for(fips_neighbor in unique(neighbors$V4)){
      
      if(length(data$synthetic_opioid_crude_death_rate[data$year == year & data$county_code == fips_neighbor]) && data$synthetic_opioid_crude_death_rate[data$year == year & data$county_code == fips_neighbor] > highest){
        highest <- data$synthetic_opioid_crude_death_rate[data$year == year & data$county_code == fips_neighbor]
      }
      
    }
    data$neighbor_highest_synthetic_opioid_death_rate[data$county_code == fips & data$year == year] <- highest
  }
  
}

data$neighbor_synthetic_outbreak[data$neighbor_highest_synthetic_opioid_death_rate >= threshold] <- T


## Imputation

for(i in 1:nrow(data)){
  for(j in 1:ncol(data)){
    if(length(data[i,j]) > 0 && !is.na(data[i,j]) && data[i,j] == -999){
      data[i,j] <- NA
    }
  }
}


data$unemployment_rate[is.na(data$unemployment_rate)] <- mean(data$unemployment_rate, na.rm = T)
data$median_household_income[is.na(data$median_household_income)] <- mean(data$median_household_income, na.rm = T)
data$median_household_income <- log(data$median_household_income)
data$proportion_poverty[is.na(data$proportion_poverty)] <- mean(data$proportion_poverty, na.rm=T)
data$proportion_male[is.na(data$proportion_male)] <- mean(data$proportion_male, na.rm=T)
data$proportion_homes_no_vehicle[is.na(data$proportion_homes_no_vehicle)] <- mean(data$proportion_homes_no_vehicle, na.rm=T)
data$proportion_uninsured[is.na(data$proportion_uninsured)] <- mean(data$proportion_uninsured, na.rm = T)
data$proportion_homeowners_35perc_income[is.na(data$proportion_homeowners_35perc_income)] <- mean(data$proportion_homeowners_35perc_income, na.rm = T)
data$proportion_high_school_or_greater[is.na(data$proportion_high_school_or_greater)] <- mean(data$proportion_high_school_or_greater, na.rm = T)
data$proportion_white[is.na(data$proportion_white)] <- mean(data$proportion_white, na.rm = T)
data$population_density <- log(data$population_density)
data$population_density[data$population_density == -Inf | is.na(data$population_density)] <- median(data$population_density, na.rm = T)


data$police_violence[is.na(data$police_violence)] <- F

The Prediction Models

Defining the Regression Equation

First, we must define a regression equation which will be fed into a series of machine learning algorithms. [describe variable choices, specifically talk about how we probably dont want to get too in the weeds about picking variables only cuz in real life we wont know exactly which variables will be the best predictors a future paper could advance variable selection procedures]


func <- next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate ~ (synthetic_opioid_crude_death_rate +
                                                   heroin_crude_death_rate +
                                                   cocaine_crude_death_rate +

Continuous Metrics

We want to calculate the MAE and RMSE of each fit. Generally, these will inform of, overall, how good at predicting each model is. The MAE is the average error of each prediction. The RMSE is similar but has an increased penalty for outliers. RMSE is always equal to or greater than MAE.


test_data <- test_data[!is.na(test_data$lr_prediction),]

MAE_lr <- 0
RMSE_lr <- 0

MAE_rf <- 0
RMSE_rf <- 0

MAE_poisson <- 0
RMSE_poisson <- 0


for(i in 1:nrow(test_data))
{
  MAE_lr <- MAE_lr + abs(test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate[i] - test_data$lr_prediction[i])
  RMSE_lr <- RMSE_lr + (test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate[i] - test_data$lr_prediction[i])^2
  
  MAE_rf <- MAE_rf + abs(test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate[i] - test_data$rf_prediction[i])
  RMSE_rf <- RMSE_rf + (test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate[i] - test_data$rf_prediction[i])^2
  
  MAE_poisson <- MAE_poisson + abs(test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate[i] - test_data$poisson_prediction[i])
  RMSE_poisson <- RMSE_poisson + (test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate[i] - test_data$poisson_prediction[i])^2
}

MAE_lr <- round(MAE_lr/nrow(test_data),3)
RMSE_lr <- round(sqrt(RMSE_lr/nrow(test_data)),3)
pearsons_lr <- round(cor(test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate, test_data$lr_prediction),3)
spearman_lr <- round(cor(test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate, test_data$lr_prediction, method = "spearman"),3)

MAE_rf <- round(MAE_rf/nrow(test_data),3)
RMSE_rf <- round(sqrt(RMSE_rf/nrow(test_data)),3)
pearsons_rf <- round(cor(test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate, test_data$rf_prediction),3)
spearman_rf <- round(cor(test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate, test_data$rf_prediction, method = "spearman"),3)

MAE_poisson <- round(MAE_poisson/nrow(test_data),3)
RMSE_poisson <- round(sqrt(RMSE_poisson/nrow(test_data)),3)
pearsons_poisson <- round(cor(test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate, test_data$poisson_prediction),3)
spearman_poisson <- round(cor(test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate, test_data$poisson_prediction, method = "spearman"),3)

results <- as.data.frame(matrix(c("Linear Regression",MAE_lr, RMSE_lr, pearsons_lr, spearman_lr),nrow=1))
results$V1 <- as.character(results$V1)
results$V2 <- as.numeric(as.character(results$V2))
results$V3 <- as.numeric(as.character(results$V3))
results$V4 <- as.numeric(as.character(results$V4))
results$V5 <- as.numeric(as.character(results$V5))

results <- rbind(results, c("Random Forest",MAE_rf,RMSE_rf, pearsons_rf, spearman_rf))
results <- rbind(results, c("Poisson Regression",MAE_poisson,RMSE_poisson, pearsons_poisson, spearman_poisson))
## use rbind to add other model results


colnames(results) <- c("Model", "MAE","RMSE","Pearson's R","Spearman's rho")

Rank-Ordering the Results

This could provide a good indication if the model is good for risk prediction. Let us do quintiles!


test_data$actual_rank[order(-test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate)] <- 1:nrow(test_data)
test_data$lr_rank[order(-test_data$lr_prediction)] <- 1:nrow(test_data)
test_data$rf_rank[order(-test_data$rf_prediction)] <- 1:nrow(test_data)
test_data$poisson_rank[order(-test_data$poisson_prediction)] <- 1:nrow(test_data)

test_data$actual_percentile <- NA
test_data$lr_percentile <- NA
test_data$rf_percentile <- NA
test_data$poisson_percentile <- NA

percentile_size <- floor(nrow(test_data)/10)

for(i in 1:10){
  
  threshold_lower <- (i-1)*percentile_size
  threshold_upper <- (i)*percentile_size
  
  test_data$actual_percentile[test_data$actual_rank > threshold_lower & test_data$actual_rank <= threshold_upper] <- i
  
  test_data$lr_percentile[test_data$lr_rank > threshold_lower & test_data$lr_rank <= threshold_upper] <- i
  
  test_data$rf_percentile[test_data$rf_rank > threshold_lower & test_data$rf_rank <= threshold_upper] <- i
  
  test_data$poisson_percentile[test_data$poisson_rank > threshold_lower & test_data$poisson_rank <= threshold_upper] <- i
}

Categorical Metrics


test_data$actual_outbreak <- F
test_data$actual_outbreak[test_data$next_year_synthetic_opioid_death_rate >= 10] <- T
test_data$lr_predict_outbreak <- F
test_data$lr_predict_outbreak[test_data$lr_prediction >= 10] <- T
test_data$rf_predict_outbreak <- F
test_data$rf_predict_outbreak[test_data$rf_prediction >= 10] <- T
test_data$poisson_predict_outbreak <- F
test_data$poisson_predict_outbreak[test_data$poisson_prediction >= 10] <- T

test_data$final_evaluation_lr <- 5
test_data$final_evaluation_rf <- 5
test_data$final_evaluation_poisson <- 5

lr_true_pos <- 0
lr_false_neg <- 0
lr_true_neg <- 0
lr_false_pos <- 0

rf_true_pos <- 0
rf_false_neg <- 0
rf_true_neg <- 0
rf_false_pos <- 0

poisson_true_pos <- 0
poisson_false_neg <- 0
poisson_true_neg <- 0
poisson_false_pos <- 0

for(i in 1:nrow(test_data)){
  
  if(test_data$actual_outbreak[i]){
    #if there is an outbreak
    if(test_data$lr_predict_outbreak[i]){
      ## true positive
      
      lr_true_pos <- lr_true_pos + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_lr[i] <- 1
      
    }else{
      ## false negative
      lr_false_neg <- lr_false_neg + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_lr[i] <- 2
    }
    if(test_data$rf_predict_outbreak[i]){
      ## true positive
      
      rf_true_pos <- rf_true_pos + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_rf[i] <- 1
      
    }else{
      ## false negative
      rf_false_neg <- rf_false_neg + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_rf[i] <- 2
    }
    if(test_data$poisson_predict_outbreak[i]){
      ## true positive
      
      poisson_true_pos <- poisson_true_pos + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_poisson[i] <- 1
      
    }else{
      ## false negative
      poisson_false_neg <- poisson_false_neg + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_poisson[i] <- 2
    }
    
  }else{
    if(test_data$lr_predict_outbreak[i]){
      ## false positive
      lr_false_pos <- lr_false_pos + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_lr[i] <- 3
    }else{
      ## true_negative
      lr_true_neg <- lr_true_neg + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_lr[i] <- 4
    }
    if(test_data$rf_predict_outbreak[i]){
      ## false positive
      rf_false_pos <- rf_false_pos + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_rf[i] <- 3
    }else{
      ## true_negative
      rf_true_neg <- rf_true_neg + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_rf[i] <- 4
    }
    if(test_data$poisson_predict_outbreak[i]){
      ## false positive
      poisson_false_pos <- poisson_false_pos + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_poisson[i] <- 3
    }else{
      ## true_negative
      poisson_true_neg <- poisson_true_neg + 1
      test_data$final_evaluation_poisson[i] <- 4
    }
  }
  
}

lr_positive_predicted_value <- round(lr_true_pos/(lr_true_pos + lr_false_pos),3)
lr_negative_predicted_value <- round(lr_true_neg/(lr_true_neg + lr_false_neg),3)
lr_sensitivity <- round(lr_true_pos/(lr_true_pos + lr_false_neg),3)
lr_specificity <- round(lr_true_neg/(lr_true_neg + lr_false_pos),3)
lr_accuracy <- round((lr_true_pos + lr_true_neg)/(lr_true_neg + lr_true_pos + lr_false_pos + lr_false_neg),3)

rf_positive_predicted_value <- round(rf_true_pos/(rf_true_pos + rf_false_pos),3)
rf_negative_predicted_value <- round(rf_true_neg/(rf_true_neg + rf_false_neg),3)
rf_sensitivity <- round(rf_true_pos/(rf_true_pos + rf_false_neg),3)
rf_specificity <- round(rf_true_neg/(rf_true_neg + rf_false_pos),3)
rf_accuracy <- round((rf_true_pos + rf_true_neg)/(rf_true_neg + rf_true_pos + rf_false_pos + rf_false_neg),3)

poisson_positive_predicted_value <- round(poisson_true_pos/(poisson_true_pos + poisson_false_pos),3)
poisson_negative_predicted_value <- round(poisson_true_neg/(poisson_true_neg + poisson_false_neg),3)
poisson_sensitivity <- round(poisson_true_pos/(poisson_true_pos + poisson_false_neg),3)
poisson_specificity <- round(poisson_true_neg/(poisson_true_neg + poisson_false_pos),3)
poisson_accuracy <- round((poisson_true_pos + poisson_true_neg)/(poisson_true_neg + poisson_true_pos + poisson_false_pos + poisson_false_neg),3)

eval_table <- as.data.frame(matrix(c("Linear Regression",lr_true_pos, lr_false_pos, lr_true_neg, lr_false_neg, lr_positive_predicted_value, lr_negative_predicted_value, lr_sensitivity, lr_specificity, lr_accuracy),nrow=1))

}
